Why PWA Wins for This Use Case
1. Target Device Reality
Zomato/Swiggy delivery partners primarily use entry-level to mid-range Android phones (Redmi, Realme, Moto G series). These users:

Are experienced with installing apps BUT have limited storage
Are comfortable opening links from WhatsApp (how platform managers share updates)
Do NOT expect gig-economy tools to require a Play Store search

2. Distribution Strategy
GigShield can be deployed to thousands of workers by simply sharing a WhatsApp message with the URL:
"Hey! Sign up for GigShield income protection: https://gigshield.in
Open in Chrome → tap 'Add to Home Screen' → Done ✅"
No App Store review delays. No apk sideloading risks. No storage constraints.
3. iOS Is Not Our Primary Market
Food delivery workers in India are overwhelmingly on Android. iOS support is a Phase 3+ concern. PWA works on iOS Safari but with limited push notification support — acceptable for MVP.
4. Rapid Iteration Advantage
During a 6-week hackathon, the ability to push fixes and improvements instantly (no app store review) is critical. PWA allows the team to update UI and fix bugs without any user action required.

