Mobile-First Design Principles

Single-column layout optimized for 360px viewport (minimum supported width)
Large tap targets: minimum 48×48px for all interactive elements
Minimal data usage: images optimized, API responses paginated
High-contrast text (accessibility for outdoor viewing in bright sunlight)
Bottom navigation bar (thumb-friendly on large phones)


Future: Native App (Phase 4+)
If GigShield scales to 100,000+ users, a native Android app (React Native) can be built using the same component logic, giving access to:

Background GPS tracking (more reliable than browser)
Native payment SDKs (Razorpay Android SDK)
Offline-first database (SQLite)

The PWA approach today does not block this path — it accelerates the path to product-market fit first.
